Act  DEGHTe
Desc A sivak draconain in black robes is standing here.  The creature has
polished silver scales and ebony black horns.  An odd feature of this
draconian are waves of metallic blue hair that start from the back of his
horns and flow down to his shoulders.  He stands approximately nine feet in
height.  His hands and feet, both bare, end in sharp talons.  His eyes are
silvery orbs and devoid of pupils.  On the center of his robes is the symbol
of a skull with a snake coiling through the mouth -- a sigil near forgotten,
representing those most loyal to the Archmage Darkahn Kiralv.  
~
Backg Krisantilith is, for the most part, an ordinary draconian.  He was
made the same way others were, through the corruption of dragon eggs.
He in particular is of the sivak caste of draconians.  His strange
appreciation for the art of magic led him away from the sterotypical
cast of the sivak warrior form.  Instead, Krisantilith chose to be
a mage of the Enchanter class.  He had little to no interaction with
the followers of Takhisis, instead choosing his own way of life.  The
Dark Queen, being what she is and having little time to deal with the
sparse deserter or two, has yet to send those loyal to her to bring
retribution to this draconian.
 
To make himself stand out and to his eyes give himself more definition
then the "mindless" draconian minions of Takhisis, Krisantilith underwent
a relatively simple spell to allow himself to grow hair like most normal
humanoid beings from the top of his head.
 
One day, while resting in the path between Palanthas and Kalaman, he had
received an unexpected visitor.  The visitor was Darkahn Kiralv, and he
approached Krisantilith with the intention of being the draconian into
the folds of the Conclave.  Krisantilith accepted and underwent the
test into the Conclave, overseen by Darkahn.  Krisantilith passed his
initiation and was accepted into the Conclave as an apprentice black robe.
 
Krisantilith rose quickly through the ranks of the Conclave, and was the
second to become the Trimorte of the Black Robes, just after Asauder.
Indeed he was well renown for being the second Trimorte, for at the
time of being granted this position, Asauder was as well still Trimorte.
This was strange only in the fact that there was only to be one such
individual with bearings of that title at a time within the black robes.
 
Krisantilith supported and assisted Darkahn in his run for Towermaster of
the Conclave.  He had deceived and mislead Serie Uth Rander, Towermistress
of the Conclave at the time, into believing strings of lies and vicious
propaganda that had caused her to act out of line of her duty.  Darkahn had
then pointed out these acts, and the Conclave as a whole had demanded Serie
denounce her title as Towermaster.  A vote was then held between the three
Ordermasters -  Darkahn, Aerogos and Shinn.  With the help of his loyal
Black Robes, Darkahn had achieved the role of Towermaster.
 
Upon Darkahn receiving the Towermaster position, he had initiated Krisantilith
into his secret fold of Magi, not loyal to the Conclave but instead loyal
to only Darkahn.  Initially, this organization was meant only for elven
and necromantic black robes within the Conclave.  Krisantilith was given as
an acception for his assistance in dethroning Serie.  Krisantilith followed
loyally after Darkahn for the many years of Darkahn's reign as Towermaster.
 
When the era came to an end, Krisantilith disappeared like many others
when Darkahn saw the end of his days as Towermaster.  He has been thought to
have since resigned from the Conclave and continued his own studies in magic.
~
